annotationA: Vacuolar protein sorting 37B, isoform A; It is involved in the biological process described with: endosome transport via multivesicular body sorting pathway
annotationB: Vacuolar-sorting protein SNF8; Larsen (Lsn), also known as Vacuolar protein sorting 22, is a member of the ESCRT-II complex, which sorts certain endocytosed receptors for degradation via the multivesicular body. As part of this complex, Lsn also has a role in bcd RNA localization
